      "message": "Update: https://skia-review.googlesource.com/c/skia/+/357436 fixes the one specific error reported in skbug.com/11205, but just leads to more errors. In particular, I think that GrVkPipelineStateDataManager will need to start overriding many of the base-class methods (much like GrMtlPipelineStateDataManager does).\n\nToday, Vk leans heavily on the base-class functionality in GrUniformDataManager, and that code is obeying the std140 packing rules. (see: https://source.chromium.org/chromium/chromium/src/+/master:third_party/skia/src/gpu/GrUniformDataManager.cpp;l\u003d306;drc\u003dbe259dcce0faaae616a790797c30045244e1b93b).\n\nSo the changes in this CL to Vk\u0027s pipeline state data manager allocate a buffer based on the std430 packing rules, but then calls to setMatrix2f (for example) obey the std140 rules, and trigger buffer overruns.",
